    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD represents a rare, collector-grade example of the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary powerplant. The engine maintains factory-spec compression across all rotor faces, with a meticulously maintained vacuum line system to ensure seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbos. The chassis is exceptionally taut, featuring the original double-wishbone suspension geometry and a Torsen limited-slip differential that preserves the vehicle's celebrated 50/50 weight distribution. Finished in factory-correct paint with no signs of clear coat failure or oxidation, the car remains mechanically stock, free from the heat-soak issues common in lesser examples. This is an investment-grade FD with a linear power delivery and an interior that retains its original bolster integrity and tactile switchgear functionality.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 19
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
